# Forge holds no model provider key of its own for chat — users bring their own
# credentials through the in-app Providers panel, and each is stored in an
# httpOnly cookie, never in the environment:
#   - a Hugging Face token for cloud chat
#   - an OpenAI-compatible connection for chat against your own provider
#   - an OpenAI-compatible connection for codegen (the AI that writes playgrounds)
#
# The ONE optional server-side key is the free codegen "taste" below. It's off by
# default: a cloned Forge without it is strictly bring-your-own.

# Optional. A Groq API key used to write a first-time visitor's first few
# playgrounds for free — the "taste" of the product before they bring their own
# codegen key. On a DEPLOY each browser gets a small fixed number of free
# generations (FREE_CODEGEN_LIMIT in lib/playground/codegen-provider.ts, tracked
# by an httpOnly cookie); everything after — regenerate, modify, new playgrounds
# — needs their own key. Running locally is never metered: it's your own key on
# your own machine. Get one at https://console.groq.com/keys
#
# You don't need this file at all to develop: bring a codegen key through the
# in-app Providers panel instead, which takes precedence over anything here.
GROQ_API_KEY=

# Set to 1 to actually turn the free tier on. GROQ_API_KEY alone does nothing.
#
# IMPORTANT: /api/codegen has no authentication. The per-browser counter cookie
# is a speed bump for honest visitors, not a control: clearing cookies resets it,
# and the endpoint can be called directly with no cookie at all. What actually
# bounds the damage depends on which Groq tier the key is on.
#
# ON GROQ'S FREE TIER there is no billing and no spend limit to set (spend limits
# are a paid-plan feature) — so you cannot be charged. The budget you can exhaust
# is RATE, and it is shared ORG-WIDE: ~30 requests/min, ~6,000 tokens/min, and
# 14,400 requests/day across every key on the account. One generation runs to
# roughly 5k tokens, so the practical ceiling is about ONE playground per minute
# for the whole deployment. Two visitors generating at once already collide, and
# the failure lands on your users as a 429, not on you as a bill.
#
# ON A PAID GROQ TIER, set a spend limit: Settings -> Billing -> Limits (the
# default is $500/month, which is almost certainly not what you want here).
#
# EITHER WAY, rate-limit /api/codegen at your edge, which is what makes scripted
# abuse pointless — the cookie never could. On Vercel: Firewall -> Custom Rules
# -> Rate Limit, keyed on IP. Match the path with EQUALS, not "starts with":
# /api/codegen-provider shares the prefix and is hit during ordinary navigation,
# so a prefix match spends the generation budget on page loads.
#
# Left unset, every user brings their own codegen provider and none of this
# applies.
FORGE_FREE_CODEGEN=
